summary: This is an FBI communication requesting that the Palm Springs Resident Agency cover a lead to interview an individual in La Quinta, California, regarding the obstruction of justice case against Alfredo Rodriguez. The individual refused to be interviewed due to a non-disclosure agreement signed with Jeffrey Epstein.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: The subject of the obstruction of justice investigation (Case ID 72-MM-113327). The document is a request to cover a lead to interview someone related to his case.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Mentioned as the prior employer of the individual who refused an FBI interview, citing a non-disclosure agreement signed with Epstein.

connections.description: Implied connection as Rodriguez is the subject of an investigation, and the document references Epstein as the prior employer of a witness who signed an NDA.

events.title: Attempted FBI interview in La Quinta
events.description: Special Agents attempted to interview an individual at a residence in La Quinta, California. The individual was not home, but mail was confirmed at the location. A phone call was made, and the individual refused the interview citing a non-disclosure agreement with Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: On January 13, 2011, FBI agents attempted to interview an individual in La Quinta, CA, related to the Alfredo Rodriguez obstruction of justice case.
The individual refused to be interviewed, citing a non-disclosure agreement signed with prior employer Jeffrey Epstein.
The document indicates the individual had moved to the Philippines and was no longer with a partner.
This shows the FBI's active investigation into obstruction of justice matters connected to Jeffrey Epstein's circle in early 2011.
The case ID 72-MM-113327 is referenced, pertaining to the investigation of Alfredo Rodriguez.
